    <h2>Adjustments for Convergences:</h2>
    <div class="caution">note: power builds benefit from the below items, while others do not. Therefore, it's recommended to bring a power build to convergences.</div>

    <h3>SotO and JW items</h3>
    These items work in both SotO and JW convergences.
    <ul>
        <li>
            <a href="https://wiki.guildwars2.com/wiki/Superior_Sigil_of_Demon_Slaying">Superior Sigil of Demon Slaying</a> - 10% damage vs Demons, Kryptis, and Titanspawn.
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="https://wiki.guildwars2.com/index.php?title=Powerful_Potion_of_Demon_Slaying">Powerful Potion of Demon Slaying</a> - 10% damage vs Demons, Kryptis, and Titanspawn. Sometimes someone will put out a <a href="https://wiki.guildwars2.com/wiki/Demon-Slaying_Station">Demon Slaying Station</a>, which gives the same enhancement.
        </li>
        <li>
            <a href="https://wiki.guildwars2.com/wiki/Relic_of_the_Eagle">Relic of the Eagle</a> - 10% damage when enemy under 50% hp. Swap to Eagle when transitioning to the third boss phase (start of 50%).
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>SotO only items</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <a href="https://wiki.guildwars2.com/wiki/Superior_Sigil_of_the_Night">Superior Sigil of Night</a> - 10% damage at night. SotO Convergences are always at night.
        </li>
    </ul>

</section>
     